4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO THE UNLAWFUL USE OF
5 AIRCRAFT FOR HUNTING; EXTENDING THE WAITING PERIOD AFTER USE OF AN AIRCRAFT; BANNING
6 THE POSSESSION OF UNMANNED AERIAL VEHICLES WHILE HUNTING; INCREASING FINES AND
7 PENALTIES; AND AMENDING SECTION 87-6-208, MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 87-6-208, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "87-6-208. Unlawful use of aircraft. (1) Except as provided in 87-3-126, a person may not:
13 (a) kill, take, or shoot at any game bird, game animal, or fur-bearing animal from an aircraft;
14 (b) use an aircraft:
15 (i) to locate any game animal for the purpose of hunting that animal during the same calendar day
16 within 48 hours after using the aircraft; or
17 (ii) for the purpose of concentrating, pursuing, driving, rallying, or stirring up any game bird,
18 migratory bird, game animal, or fur-bearing animal; or
19 (c) if in or using an aircraft, spot or locate any game animal or fur-bearing animal and
20 communicate the location of the game animal or fur-bearing animal to any person:
21 (i) on the ground by means of any air-to-ground communication signal or other device as an aid to
22 hunting or pursuing wildlife; or
23 (ii) within the same calendar day 48 hours after using the aircraft; or
24 (d) hunt or attempt to hunt any game bird, game animal, or fur-bearing animal while in possession
25 of an unmanned aerial vehicle.
26 (2) The provisions of this section do not apply:
27 (a) during emergency situations;
28 (b) when search and rescue operations are being conducted; or
