3 (a) Unless otherwise provided in this subsection (3), a person convicted of a violation of this
4 section shall be fined not less than $300 $3,000 or more than $1,000 $10,000 or be imprisoned in the county
5 detention center for not more than 6 months, or both. In addition, the person, upon conviction or forfeiture of
6 bond or bail, may be subject to forfeiture of any current hunting, fishing, or trapping license issued by this state
7 and the privilege to hunt, fish, or trap in this state or to use state lands, as defined in 77-1-101, for recreational
8 purposes for a period of time set by the court for 36 months from the date of conviction or forfeiture unless the
9 court imposes a longer period.
10 (b) If a person is convicted or forfeits bond or bail after being charged with unlawful use of an
11 aircraft to kill or take a deer, elk, antelope, mountain lion, mountain sheep, moose, wild buffalo, caribou,
12 mountain goat, black bear, or grizzly bear, the person shall be fined not less than $500 $5,000 or more than
13 $2,000 $20,000 or be imprisoned in the county detention center for not more than 6 months, or both. In
14 addition, the person shall forfeit any current hunting, fishing, recreational use, or trapping license issued by this
15 state and the privilege to hunt, fish, or trap in this state for 30 36 months from the date of conviction or forfeiture
16 unless the court imposes a longer period.
17 (c) If a person is convicted or forfeits bond or bail after being charged with unlawful use of an
18 aircraft to kill or take a fur-bearing animal, the person shall be fined not less than $100 $1,000 or more than
19 $1,000 $10,000 or be imprisoned in the county detention center for not more than 6 months, or both. In
20 addition, the person shall forfeit any current hunting, fishing, recreational use, or trapping license issued by this
21 state and the privilege to hunt, fish, or trap in this state for 24 36 months from the date of conviction or forfeiture
22 unless the court imposes a longer period, and any pelts possessed unlawfully must be confiscated.
23 (4) As used in this section, "aircraft" has the meaning provided in 87-6-101."
